  "text": "# Envoy Access Logging Infrastructure Audit (v1.31.2)\n\n## Summary\n\nThis audit covers the access logging infrastructure in Envoy v1.31.2 and data-plane-api. The infrastructure consists of access log sink implementations, access log filters, and their corresponding proto definitions.\n\n## Access Log Sink Implementations\n\n### 1. File Access Logger\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/file/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/file/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/file_access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/file_access_log_impl.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** YES - FULLY SUPPORTED\n- Supports deprecated json_format field (google.protobuf.Struct, values as strings)\n- Supports deprecated typed_json_format field (google.protobuf.Struct with typed values)\n- Supports log_format field (config.core.v3.SubstitutionFormatString, which supports JSON)\n- Implementation in config.cc (lines 31-60) handles all three format cases and creates appropriate formatters\n\n### 2. Stream Access Loggers (stdout/stderr)\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/stream/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/stream_access_log_common_impl.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** YES - SUPPORTED VIA SUBSTITUTION FORMAT STRING\n- Uses log_format field (config.core.v3.SubstitutionFormatString)\n- SubstitutionFormatString supports both text and JSON formats\n- Implementation delegates to createStreamAccessLogInstance template (stream_access_log_common_impl.h:14-31)\n\n### 3. Fluentd Access Logger\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/fluentd_access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/fluentd_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/substitution_formatter.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/substitution_formatter.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** YES - STRUCTURED JSON FORMAT\n- Uses google.protobuf.Struct record field for structured logging\n- Implementation in config.cc (lines 63-69) creates a JSON formatter\n- Converts JSON to MessagePack format for Fluentd Forward Protocol\n- Supports nested JSON objects and typed values (string, number, boolean)\n- Includes formatters support for custom formatting (line 64)\n\n### 4. gRPC Access Logger (HTTP)\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/config_utils.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/config_utils.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/grpc_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/grpc_access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/grpc_access_log_proto_descriptors.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/grpc_access_log_proto_descriptors.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger_clients.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger_utils.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger_utils.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** NO - STRUCTURED PROTOBUF\n- Sends structured protobuf messages (HTTPAccessLogEntry) not text or JSON\n- Uses envoy::data::accesslog::v3::HTTPAccessLogEntry for HTTP logs\n- Uses envoy::service::accesslog::v3::StreamAccessLogsMessage for batching\n- Binary protobuf format, not human-readable JSON or text\n\n### 5. gRPC Access Logger (TCP)\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** NO - STRUCTURED PROTOBUF\n- Sends structured protobuf messages (TCPAccessLogEntry) not text or JSON\n- Uses envoy::data::accesslog::v3::TCPAccessLogEntry for TCP logs\n- Uses envoy::service::accesslog::v3::StreamAccessLogsMessage for batching\n- Binary protobuf format, not human-readable JSON or text\n\n### 6. OpenTelemetry Access Logger\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/grpc_access_log_impl.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/grpc_access_log_impl.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_proto_descriptors.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/access_log_proto_descriptors.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/substitution_formatter.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/substitution_formatter.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** NO - STRUCTURED OPENTELEMETRY LOGS\n- Sends structured OpenTelemetry Log Resource messages (not text or JSON)\n- Uses opentelemetry.proto.logs.v1.LogResource format\n- Supports custom body (opentelemetry.proto.common.v1.AnyValue) and attributes (KeyValueList)\n- Binary OpenTelemetry protobuf format\n- Can transport various structured data types but not plain text/JSON\n\n### 7. WASM Access Logger\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/wasm_access_log_impl.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**JSON Support:** DEPENDS ON WASM IMPLEMENTATION\n- Configuration delegates to PluginConfig for WASM module (envoy/extensions/wasm/v3/wasm.proto)\n- Implementation in config.cc creates WasmAccessLog which calls into WASM VM\n- Format depends entirely on the WASM module's implementation\n- Cannot determine JSON support without analyzing specific WASM modules\n\n## Access Log Filters\n\n### CEL Expression Filter\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n**Implementation Files:**\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/config.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/config.h\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.cc\n- source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.h\n\n**Proto Definition:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto (data-plane-api)\n\n**Note:** This is an access log FILTER, not a sink. It evaluates CEL expressions to determine whether an access log should be emitted.\n\n## Base Classes and Common Infrastructure\n\n**Repository:** github.com/sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2\n\n### Core Access Log Framework\n1. **source/common/access_log/access_log_impl.h** - Core filter classes:\n   - FilterFactory: Creates filters from proto configuration\n   - StatusCodeFilter, DurationFilter, ComparisonFilter\n   - OperatorFilter, AndFilter, OrFilter\n   - NotHealthCheckFilter, TraceableRequestFilter, RuntimeFilter\n   - HeaderFilter, ResponseFlagFilter, GrpcStatusFilter\n   - LogTypeFilter, MetadataFilter\n   - AccessLogFactory: Creates access log instances from proto\n\n2. **source/common/access_log/access_log_manager_impl.cc/h** - Access log manager and file handling\n\n### Common Access Logger Base and Utilities\n1. **source/extensions/access_loggers/common/access_log_base.cc/h** - ImplBase class for all access loggers\n2. **source/extensions/access_loggers/common/file_access_log_impl.cc/h** - FileAccessLog implementation\n3. **source/extensions/access_loggers/common/stream_access_log_common_impl.h** - Template for stream logging\n4. **source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger.h** - Template for gRPC access loggers\n5. **source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger_clients.h** - gRPC client interfaces\n6. **source/extensions/access_loggers/common/grpc_access_logger_utils.cc/h** - gRPC utilities\n\n## Proto Definitions (data-plane-api)\n\n**File Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/file/v3/file.proto\n**Stream Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stream/v3/stream.proto\n**Fluentd Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto\n**gRPC Access Log (ALS):** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/grpc/v3/als.proto\n**OpenTelemetry Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto\n**WASM Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto\n**CEL Filter:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto\n**Process Rate Limit Filter:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto\n**Dynamic Modules Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto (proto only, no C++ impl)\n**Stats Access Log:** envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto (proto only, no C++ impl)\n\n## JSON Logging Support Summary\n\n**Full JSON Support:**\n1. File Access Logger - Explicit JSON support via json_format, typed_json_format, and SubstitutionFormatString\n2. Stream Access Loggers (stdout/stderr) - JSON via SubstitutionFormatString\n3. Fluentd Access Logger - Structured JSON format (converted to MessagePack)\n\n**Structured Binary Format (Not JSON/Text):**\n1. gRPC Access Logger (HTTP & TCP) - Binary protobuf (HTTPAccessLogEntry, TCPAccessLogEntry)\n2. OpenTelemetry Access Logger - Binary OpenTelemetry protobuf format\n\n**Implementation-Dependent:**\n1. WASM Access Logger - Depends on WASM module implementation\n\n**Filters Only (Not Log Sinks):**\n1. CEL Expression Filter - Filters whether logs are emitted\n\n**Proto Only (No C++ Implementation):**\n1. Dynamic Modules Access Logger - Proto definition exists but no C++ factory/implementation in v1.31.2\n2. Stats Access Logger - Proto definition exists but no C++ factory/implementation in v1.31.2\n3. Process Rate Limit Filter - Filter implementation, not a sink\n"
}

